{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"609ee4a2-b70d-4d1b-bbed-284456a0e356","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's a general guide for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Configure NuGet.org\nOn **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**, add a new GitHub Actions publisher:\n- **Repository owner** / **Repository name**\n- **Workflow filename** (e.g. `publish.yml`)\n- Optionally restrict to an **environment** (recommended)\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n```yaml\n# Add permissions at the job level\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    # Optional but recommended: tie to a GitHub environment\n    environment: nuget-publish\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # Install .NET SDK that supports trusted publishing (8.0.400+)\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      # Build & pack as before\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # Push — no API key needed!\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push \"**/*.nupkg\"\n              --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | No secret needed |\n| `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | Remove the `--api-key` flag entirely |\n| No `permissions` block | Add `id-token: write` |\n| .NET SDK any version | .NET SDK **8.0.400+** (first version with OIDC support) |\n\n### 3. Clean up\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once verified.\n\nThe .NET SDK automatically detects the GitHub Actions OIDC environment and exchanges the token with NuGet.org — no explicit token-fetching step required.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5dd859b3-f996-49a2-8493-90324d9a9ba9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. I don't have a specific workflow file to look at, so I'll provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":591},"id":"be7a7b15-c28d-4d00-9674-b5bb57e82a3d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:42:02.360Z","parentId":"11d5e967-5fe2-4f44-94fd-084864ed9e6e"}
